      <div class="msgContentFrame">Even if SE fixes the game, puts in an AH and streamlines the UI there STILL is no incentive to play.  <br /> <br />What cool gear can I get? Leves should give good incentives (GEAR). At least for the first time you do them. Also make more leves. After doing the same leves over and over for 8 levels you want to pull your hair out. Conversely mobs should drop more gear. Oh, and that gear shouldn't need to get repaired. In fact get rid of the entire repair system. <br /> <br />Why am I leveling? There is no end game obviously, but really there's nothing in between either. This WILL come in time I'm sure, however other than the story there's nothing currently to participate in. FFXI had sub job quests, the chocobo quest and Rank quests. Later on there were the advanced job quests, gobbie bags just to name a few. However I'll reiterate that I'm sure these things WILL come, but why weren't they in the game from the beginning?  <br /> <br />How can I level? I can't grind solo because mob density is borked. Also I can't tell if I'm going to get a set amount of SP per kill. I could get 200 for a green or 50 for a yellow...Really? Also the party system looks OK, but only after the community has to explain it! In any case at this time in FFXI I was in TONS of PUGS leveling up, here I'm still soloing for 50 SP. The aforementioned leves are OK and somewhat fun, however you're traveling wild distances doing the SAME leves over and over again. It's very monotonous especially for no progression. In other games (including offline FF games) you travel to new areas along with your quests. There is none of that here. Oh, and I don't want to craft. I do like the crafting system but on principle I feel that SE's less-than-invisible hand is forcing us to craft. No thank you. Put content in your games for us who like to kill stuff or we'll cancel, oh wait, I already did. <br /> <br />Where else is there to go? At level 20 it is as though I've seen most of the world, or at least it seems like it. The ease of travel or lack of diversity ruins that sense of mystery of undiscovered lands. In FFXI I felt like I was exploring new lands excited to board the ship from Selbina to Mhaura. Here there is none of that. I'll assume that SE purposefully allowed this sort of what I would call over exploration due to the lack of content. <br /> <br />Now most of these things are subjective, however I think they are vital in the way most people play. There needs to be a grind that is doable and rewards that push you to play. There is NONE of that right now. <br /> <br />The only things that will fix this game for me is effort and time on SE's part. I'm optimistic on the former, but the latter is running out. <br /> <br /><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/350177.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
