      <div class="msgContentFrame">#1 Better UI and controls. This includes less menu lag, less cumbersome options, optional text and menu size regardless of screen and resolution size, more intuitive controls, more intuitive menus, more keyboard shortcuts instead of menus and most importantly allow better mouse/keyboard controls/options. When I 1st started FFXIV, I felt tired and inefficient after 6 hours of play time just because of the menus and the mouse/keyboard movement. <br /> <br />#2 Auction House or something close. The current FFXIV market is like walking into a storage room where everything is in the same white boxes with no label. By the time you reach the end of the storage room, you'll forget what's in the 1st white box. Going around to check every retainer in every market ward isn't productive. Some people take pleasure in window shopping around the NPCs but I don't want to spend all day looking for the best deals in an super laggy area. By the time I want to return to the last 'best deal' NPC, I can't find him anymore or I later found someone else selling the item at a much lower price. Unless there is an option that allows you to browse, search and buy items without checking the NPCs, I'm not going to the market ward. <br /> <br />#3 More NPC selling equipments at decent price or equipment rewards. Player run economy is cool and everything but with the current dwindling player base, bad market system and bad UI, looking for a piece of decent equipment or even repair your current one requires bending backwards and do a back flip. Starting out players are pretty clueless about everything and many will find the market very intimidating. I didn't check the FFXI AH system until I reached lv16 and currently I don't check the FFXIV market at all. NPC traders will be the life-line for new players moving from offline game to online games. If they can't find the equipments from NPC, they might just quit before checking out the player market place. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 25th 2010  1:42pm by Oddwaffle </span></i></div>
