      <div class="msgContentFrame">1.  Regarding market wards:  Please introduce a ratio for bazaar items of at least 3 to 1 so that people must post at least 3 ward specific items before they can post random junk like moko grass and gridanian walnuts in lets say the battlecraft ward for example. <br /> <br />2. Regarding market wards: Please implement a RSS feed for retainers, I noticed that ther eis a RSS for player info popular comunity sites like YG.com utilize these to extract your information and ZAM also does for Player Sigs.  These feeds could be used for Comunity sites to update comunity hosted Auction house equivilents like the most popular one on FFXIV.YG.COM.  Which i think is a godsend.  I am very pelased that a Comunity site has stepped up for this level of organization since SE seems unwilling to Give us an AH or rush any implementation of market ward search. <br /> <br />3. Regarding SP:  Please reintroduce the previous SP system with two tweaks, add in a minimum SP value of 60-75 and allow for us to use our skillz and moves and sure the luck to gain our points and hit the previous cap of 500.  The second tweak would be to increase the proc rate of the SP gains when solo.  They always seemed terrible solo as conjurer but i never had a problem hitting 400-500 in a party just casting cure and buffs.   <br /> <br />Sure sometimes SP was terribad but with these simple changes it would improove alot and alot of the comunity backlash related to SP will go away instantly.   <br /> <br />Anyways i thought I owed you guys a positive post since i have been very negative lately especially regarding SP (i really liked the old system despite its major flaws). I thought that the previous system could be fixed and easily salvaged and was shocked at the new changes they introduced regarding SP.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/290155.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /> 