 find item, click item, click sell again, get price, click sell again..... in my opinion simply clicking sell on the vendor should open up a sell window where things are already priced and then simply need to click once to sell it. twice if its a stack and you wanna sell 6 of your 7 cookies or something. possibly add a buyback feature just incase someone clicks the wrong item.  <br /> <br />4:- yes i know its top 3 but Fatigue. my only real gripe with this is i havent played my pugilist for like a week today being saturday i thought id spend a few hours killing stuffs and seemingly got crushed within couple of hours by the fatigue gone from getting 300sps to 100 within 2-3 ranks constantly fighting green mobs. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Dec  4th 2010 11:51am by Dzian </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=7144129" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=7144129"><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1406977.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /></a></div></div>
