      <div class="msgContentFrame">1. Streamline the menu system. Generally speaking, having to click multiple times to do an action is silly. In particular, the crafting menu systems can be cut down drastically. If I am on blacksmith there should be a list of every recipe I can do for my level, kind of like a spell list from FFXI. Easy recipes should be green, moderate should be yellow, will need synth support should be red, if the synth is too high and will fail 100% of the time you wont be able to select it from the list to synth. Next to each recipe name in the list there will be a number (1-99) of how many you can craft with the number of mats you currently have in your inventory, and the recipe will tell you which mats you need to synth it. I despise having to search online websites for materials for a synth, it shouldn't be a damn mystery. Also the list of every recipe you can craft should stay open from the start of the craft session so I don't have to open it every dang time! I hate to give WoW credit but the crafting UI was simple, easy, and consumed only as much time as it took to craft X item Y times. 75% of my crafting time shouldn't be clicking menus. <br /> <br />2. Auction house! Oh and please don't put it in the Adventures Guild, enough lag there already. <br /> <br />3. Repairing armor/weapons. They take damage way to fast and repairing them takes way too much time, have several NPCs in each town that repair all items in your inventory all at once, scaled by the level of the items. Also allow for PCs to repair things individually from the NPCs. If people want to save gil repairing through crafting fine. Just don't make it cost obscene amounts. <br /> <br />4. Add quests at various levels (ie 10, 15, 20, 30, 40) that lower the leve reset time for battlecraft leves, I don't include crafting/HELM ones because if an AH is introduced it would help to keep itemlevel/quantity/supply in some kind of check to keep prices at a reasonable level so people can make some profit.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1822421.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
