      <div class="msgContentFrame">1. <u>Extra retainers/craftable storage space/more storage space:</u> <br /> <br />Our equipped armor/weapons use up storage space. <br />Our crafting tools use up storage space. <br />Our repair mats use up storage space. <br />There are a few thousand items that drop in this game. <br />We need real storage capacity now, not later. <br /> <br />2. <u>Implement a seperate screen for crafting/gathering tools:</u> <br /> <br />This would be its own screen, listing all of the crafting/gathering professions, and which primary/secondary tools you currently have for each. Once your tools are on your body, they would go in to that screen and no longer count towards your available storage space. <br />There are currently 11 crafting/gathering professions, each utilizing a minimum of 2 tools, with fishing utilizing more. <br />That's a minimum of <b>22 tools </b> that we keep up with. With bait/lures we are actually looking at 24 slots of tools. <br />That is truly worthy of its own system. <br /> <br />3. <u>NPC-Initiated Quests</u>. <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Here's to hoping that they read this thread. </span></i> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Dec  6th 2010  9:35am by ThinkDeeply </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1818162.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
