      <div class="msgContentFrame">1. Auction House -&gt; Best Idea I can think of is using the market wards to house an auction house in each ward. And you can still have bazaars. It'll be like Jeuno in every ward. Anyways, if they can't do that implement a search feature that filters out the retainers, and the only ones left are those who have &quot;Moko Grass&quot; Etc.  <br /> <br />2. Linkshell Controls - Real Linkshell Controls, where you can Kick anyone at anytime, or promote at any time. Having 20 extra slots taken up because I can't delete people just plain sucks! <br /> <br />3. Mini-quests: Small quests that give insight in the lives of the people in Eorzea. I recieved a lot more fulfillment in these than I did in the main storyline. I remember doing as many quests as I could in windurst to get fame, and at the same time got to know those npcs around me. It was really fun. <div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1819051.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
