      <div class="msgContentFrame">1. Content that can't be done solo. This game needs a community and right now there really isn't one, beyond communities formed prior to playing. Raids, missions, NMs, whatever, just give us something that you need help with. <br /> <br />2. Content that draws us into the world. Quests, basically. The only npcs we talk to now are the ones we have to talk to for leves, because all the other npcs are so flat and lifeless and pointless that we don't care about them. Give us a reason to care about this world. leve-quests don't cut it. <br /> <br />3. Bite the bullet and give us ffxi keyboard functionality. Let me control the damn camera with the arrow keys, or make a voke macro that ONLY targets mobs. The challenge of group combat shouldn't come from fighting the controls. tie the second and third command lines to alt and ctrl so we don't have to use your sh*tty macros in the first place, or worry about cycling through the command lines to make sure we are on the right one. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Dec  8th 2010  2:13pm by F3rth </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/top?cicuid=1897972" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/top?cicuid=1897972"><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1800135.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /></a> <br />Retainer: Ferthmart <br />FFXI: Ferth - Cerbereus Nee Hades Nee Leviathan.</div></div>
